race.comment: IMPENDING FURY (8) was stiff not to break through last start when beaten only a long neck and continues to build the right way this prep. Looks ready to shed the tag with even luck. EL RENO (12) took a big step forward at Warrnambool when settling handier and sticking on well to just miss the frame. Third-up and drawn to get every favour from the inside, he looms as a genuine threat. SHE'S THE RUMOUR (11) had been catching the eye from off the speed before being ridden more prominently in town last start, where she fought on strongly to hold second. Now at peak fitness and keeping Milnes, she's set for another bold showing. VIVID REASONING (6) is mixing his form but his best is certainly good enough. Couldn't convert as favourite last time, but a repeat of that run has him right in the mix. He'll just need a touch of luck from the wide alley.
